Terminalia. Tergum VII longitudinally plicate; posteriorly weakly sclerotized and mesally with sparsely arranged, longer setae. Sternum VIII (
Figure 15C
) with posterior arms jointly widely pentagonal, lateral margin subparallel along anterior half, triangularly converging along posterior half, triangular region with irregularly arranged setae of variable lengths. Spermatheca (
Figure 15D
) V-shaped to?-shaped; ramus very short, nearly contiguous with collum (corpus short); collum slightly projected, orientation slightly angled in relation to ramus; cornu (apical half) slightly arcuate, apically gradually narrowed, acute.
